{"build_type":"executable","description":"Step probe for the no-sleep event-driven model: create a monotonic timerfd armed for 200 milliseconds, build a pollfd watching it for readability, then block in poll waiting for the timer EVENT (not a sleep). When poll returns, read the timerfd expiration count and emit poll_ready (number of ready descriptors), revents (the returned event mask low byte, POLLIN is one), and timer_reads (bytes read from the timerfd, eight on success). Validates timerfd_create, timerfd_settime, and poll in this runtime.","module_name":"validate-timer-event-without-blocking-sleep","package_name":"validate-timer-event-without-blocking-sleep","function_definitions":{"validate-timer-event-without-blocking-sleep":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c32","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":32},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"fivethousand","variable_type":"i64","assignme